            "transcript": "Test 4\n\nPart 2 Questions 6-10\n\nFor each question, choose the correct answer.\n\nThe people below all want to spend a day on a tourist railway, an old-fashioned railway only used by tourists nowadays.\n\nOn the opposite page there are eight descriptions of tourist railways.\n\nDecide which tourist railway would be the most suitable for the people below.\n\nHikari and her family want to travel on a tourist railway which goes through a variety of landscapes. They'd like to have a meal at one of the stations and buy a souvenir, too.\n\nMillie and her family want to go on a tourist railway that has been in famous films, and have refreshments on the train. She'd like to travel along the coast.\n\nOlaf wants a tourist railway with entertainment for children at stations and someone on the train to tell passengers about what they see along the way. His mother and father would like a family discount.\n\nMario and his family want a tourist railway with an exhibition about its history at one of the stations, and to stay overnight nearby. They'd like to know what it’s like to drive an old-fashioned train.\n\nSerge wants to celebrate his birthday with his family on a tourist railway train, They'd like to see some wildlife from the train, and do a fun competition together, too.\n\n10\n\n64 => (9 p. 132|"
